Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of treated patients and of mortalities, due to rabies, in the Yangon General Hospital during the 1st 8 months of 2018 seems to be similar or slightly lower than last year's [2017] figures.

Myanmar's annual reports to the OIE on predominant zoonotic diseases, since 2011, included the following countrywide figures as related to rabies (human fatalities):
2011 (244. fatalities)
2012 (186)
2013 (176)
2014 (126)
2015 (93)
2016 (94)
2017 (73)
- Mod.AS

